obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (1690)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1690&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Prevention and Control`
  line `of Infectious and Contagious Diseases in Animals ^1[Act, 2009].`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint;`
  line `and different dates may be appointed for different States or for different areas therein as well as for`
  line `different provisions of this Act, and any reference in any such provision of this Act to the commencement`
  line `of this Act shall be construed in relation to any State or area or provision as a reference to the coming into`
  line `force of this Act or, as the case may be, of that provision, in such State or area.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 2018, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "Bill, 2009" (w.e.f. 5-1-2018).`
  line
  line `2. 25th August, 2009, vide notification No S.O. 2158(E), dated 24th August, 2009, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `This Act shall come into force in all the States and Union territories except the State of Uttar Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (1691)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1691&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "animal" means,--`
  line
  line `(i) cattle, buffalo, sheep, goat, yak, mithun;`
  line
  line `(ii) dog, cat, pig, horse, camel, ass, mule, poultry, bees; and`
  line
  line `(iii) any other animal or bird as the Central Government may, by notification, ^1`
  line specify;
  line
  line `(b) "Check Post" means any place established as such by the Director to carry out checking of`
  line `animals for the purpose of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "Competent Officer" means any person or officer of the Government notified as a Competent`
  line `Officer under section 17;`
  line
  line `(d) "compulsory vaccination" means vaccination of any animal against any scheduled disease in`
  line `respect of which vaccination is made mandatory under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "controlled area" means any local area which has been declared as such by the State`
  line `Government under sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(f) "defective vaccine" means any vaccine which is expired, breach in seal, contaminated,`
  line `improperly stored, unlabelled or with mutilated label;`
  line
  line `(g) "Director", in relation to a State, means any officer in charge of the Department of Animal`
  line `Husbandry or Veterinary Services, or both, notified by the State Government as such for the purpose`
  line `of this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "free area" means any controlled area which has been declared as such under sub-section (5)`
  line `of section 6;`
  line
  line `(i) "infected animal" means an animal which is infected with any scheduled disease;`
  line
  line `(j) "infected area" means an area declared as such under section 20;`
  line
  line `(k) "notification" means notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(l) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) "publication" includes propagation of information through the media or newspaper or any`
  line `other mass media and the means of local communication such as declaration in loud voice and by`
  line `beating drums in the area;`
  line
  line `(n) "Quarantine Camp" means any place declared to carry out quarantine of animals and birds for`
  line `the purpose of this Act;`
  line
  line `(o) "scheduled disease" means any disease included in the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(p) "Veterinarian" means a person having a recognised veterinary qualification who, under the`
  line `law for the time being in force, is allowed to treat animal diseases;`
  line
  line `(q) "Veterinary Officer" means any officer, appointed as such by the State Government under`
  line `clause (b) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(r) "Village Officer", in relation to a village, means any person who is authorised or designated as`
  line `such in accordance with the qualifications prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The "fish, molluse, crustacean and amphibian" shall be aquatic animals within the definition of "animal"`
  line `defined under clause (a) vide notification No. S.O. 995(E), dated 1st April, 2014.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (1692)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Appointment of Veterinary Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1692&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by notification, appoint--`
  line
  line `(a) such number of persons, as it deems proper, to be Veterinarians to undertake inspection and`
  line `specifying the local limits of their respective jurisdiction; and`
  line
  line `(b) such number of Veterinarians, as it deems proper, to be Veterinary Officers, who shall`
  line `exercise their powers and discharge their duties within the local limits of their jurisdiction as may be`
  line `specified in the said notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (1693)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Reporting scheduled diseases obligatory.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1693&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every owner, or any other person,`
  line `non-governmental organisation, public bodies or the village panchayat, in charge of any animal which he`
  line `or it has reason to believe to be infective of a scheduled disease shall report the fact to the Village Officer`
  line `or village panchayat in-charge, who may report the same in writing to the nearest available Veterinarian.`
  line
  line `(2) The Village Officer shall visit the area falling within his jurisdiction for reporting any outbreak of`
  line `the disease.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Veterinarian shall, on receipt of a report under sub-section (1), or otherwise, if he has`
  line `reason to believe that any animal is infected with a scheduled disease, report the matter to the Veterinary`
  line Officer.
  line
  line `(4) Where in any State there is any occurrence of scheduled disease in relation to any animal, the`
  line `Director shall send an intimation to the Directors of the States which are in the immediate neighbourhood`
  line `of the place where there is such occurrence, for taking appropriate preventive measures against the spread`
  line `of the disease.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (1694)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Duty to segregate infected animals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1694&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every owner or person in charge of an animal, which he`
  line `has reason to believe is infective of a scheduled disease, shall segregate such animal and have it kept in a`
  line `place away from all other animals which are healthy, and take all possible steps to prevent the infected`
  line `animal from coming in contact with any other animal.`
  line
  line `(2) The owner or other person in charge of, or having control over, the animal referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) shall confine that animal and prevent it from grazing in a common place or to drink water`
  line `from any common source including a vessel, pond, lake or river.`
  line
  line `(3) All other infected animals shall be segregated by the Municipality, Panchayat or other local`
  line administration.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (1695)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Notification of controlled areas and free areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1695&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, with the object`
  line `of preventing, controlling or eradicating any scheduled disease, by notification, declare any area to be a`
  line `controlled area in respect of any scheduled disease affecting any species of animal and any other species`
  line `that may be susceptible to the disease specified in the said notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall also cause the substance of the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1) to be published in a local newspaper in the vernacular language and by declaration in loud`
  line `voice and by beating drums in the area.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a notification has been issued under sub-section (1), all animals of the species in the`
  line `controlled area shall be subjected to compulsory vaccination against that disease, and be subjected to such`
  line `other measures against the disease, in such manner and within such time as the State Government, may,`
  line `by public notice, direct.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government shall make available necessary vaccine and it shall be obligatory on the`
  line `part of every owner, or the person in charge of an animal which is required to be vaccinated under`
  line `sub-section (3), to get the animal compulsorily vaccinated.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the State Government is satisfied, on a report received from the Director or otherwise, that,`
  line `in any controlled area, any of the scheduled diseases affecting any species of animal is no longer`
  line `prevalent, it may, by notification, declare the area to be a free area in respect of that disease in relation to`
  line `the particular species of animal.`
  line
  line `(6) Where a notification has been issued under sub-section (5), no animal of the species or of any`
  line `other susceptible species with regard to which it is a free area shall be allowed to enter the free area unless`
  line `duly immunized by vaccination against that particular disease.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (1696)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Prohibition of movement of animals from controlled area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1696&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a notification has been`
  line `issued under sub-section (1) of section 6 declaring any area as a controlled area in relation to any disease`
  line `affecting any species of animals, no animal belonging to that species shall be moved from the place where`
  line `it is kept.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director may, for the purpose of control, prevention or eradication of any scheduled disease,`
  line `in respect of any area, by order published in the Official Gazette, prohibit the movement of all animals`
  line `belonging to any species specified therein, from the place where it is kept, to any other place.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be deemed to prohibit--`
  line
  line `(a) the movement of any animal referred to therein, from the place where it is kept, to the nearest`
  line `place where it can be got vaccinated, so long as the animal is being moved for the purpose of its`
  line `immunization by vaccination; or`
  line
  line `(b) the movement of any such animal, so long as it is accompanied by a valid certificate of`
  line `vaccination to indicate that the animal is duly immunized against the particular disease and it bears`
  line `proper mark of such vaccination.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (1697)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Vaccination, marking and issue of vaccination certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1697&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The vaccine to an animal may`
  line `be administered by any person competent under the law for the time being in force to administer it, and`
  line `issue a certificate of administration of vaccination.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any animal has been vaccinated for any scheduled disease in compliance with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1), the person vaccinating the animal shall cause to put a mark by branding,`
  line `tattooing or ear tagging, or in such other manner as the Director may, by general or special order, direct`
  line `and the same shall, unless otherwise specified by the Director, shall not be removed.`
  line
  line `(3) The authority issuing a certificate of vaccination shall specify the date of vaccination, dates of`
  line `manufacture and expiry of the vaccine and the date up to which the vaccination of the animal with the`
  line `particular vaccine shall be valid.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (1698)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Contents of vaccination certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1698&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Every vaccination certificate issued under this Act shall be`
  line `in such form and shall contain such particulars as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (1699)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Entry and exit of animals into controlled area and free area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1699&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any area has been`
  line `declared as a controlled area under sub-section (1) of section 6 in respect of any disease affecting any`
  line `species of animals, no animal belonging to that species shall be taken out of, or brought into that area save`
  line `as provided in section 16.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director may, by notice duly published in the Official Gazette and at least in one daily local`
  line `newspaper in vernacular language, extend the prohibition contained in sub-section (1) to any other species`
  line `of animals, if animals belonging to that species are also likely to be infected with that disease.`
  line
  line `(3) No carrier of goods or animal shall carry any animal from or out of a controlled area, free area or`
  line `infected area by land, sea or air unless he complies with the provisions of section 16.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing contained in sub-sections (1) to (3) shall apply to the carriage by railway of any animal`
  line `referred to in those sub-sections through any area which, for the time being, is declared as a controlled`
  line `area or infected area so long as the animal is not unloaded (for whatsoever purpose or duration) in any`
  line `place within that area:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, by notification, declare that any species of animal so carried`
  line `through any local area within the State shall be duly immunized against such scheduled disease, in such`
  line `manner and within such time as may be specified in that notification and a certificate of vaccination shall`
  line `be a pre-requisite for the transportation of the animals by the railways through that area:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, where any notification as referred to in the first proviso has been issued, it shall`
  line `be incumbent on the State Government to intimate that fact to the concerned railway authorities so as to`
  line `enable them to satisfy themselves about the immunization of the animal before transporting it through the`
  line `local area of the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (1700)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Precautionary measures in relation to controlled areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1700&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `No person shall take out of the`
  line `controlled area--`
  line
  line `(a) any animal, alive or dead, which is infected with, or reasonably suspected to have been`
  line `infected with, any scheduled disease notified under sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) any kind of fodder, bedding or other material which has come into contact with any animal`
  line `infected with such disease or could, in any manner, carry the infection of the notified disease; or`
  line
  line `(c) the carcass, skin or any other part or product of such animal.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (1701)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Prohibition of markets, fairs, exhibition, etc., in the controlled areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1701&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `No person,`
  line `organisation or institution shall hold any animal market, animal fair, animal exhibition and carry on any`
  line `other activity which involves grouping or gathering of any species of animals within a controlled area:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Competent Officer may, suo motu or on application made to him in this behalf,`
  line `relax the prohibition in relation to any species of animals, in a case where animals belonging to that`
  line `species are not susceptible to the scheduled disease and are incapable of carrying it, if he is satisfied that`
  line `in the public interest it is necessary to accord such relaxation.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (1702)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Prohibition of bringing of infected animals into market and other places.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1702&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `No person shall`
  line `bring or attempt to bring into market, fair, exhibition or other congregation of animals or to any public`
  line `place, any animal which is known to be infected with a scheduled disease.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (1703)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Check Posts and Quarantine Camps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1703&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director may establish as many Quarantine`
  line `Camps and Check Posts within the State as may be required--`
  line
  line `(a) for the detention of animals suffering from any scheduled disease or of animals which have`
  line `come into contact with or have been kept in the proximity of any such infected animal;`
  line
  line `(b) for ensuring the prevention of entry into or exit from any controlled area or infected area or`
  line `free area, of any animal belonging to the species of animals in respect of which a notification, issued`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 6, or an order issued under sub-section (2) of section 7, is in force.`
  line
  line `(2) Any animal which is required to be detained, inspected, vaccinated, or marked, may be kept in the`
  line `Quarantine Camp for such period as the Competent Officer may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) Every animal detained at a Quarantine Camp shall be under the custody of the person in charge of`
  line `the camp, and shall be vaccinated and marked.`
  line
  line `(4) The officer in charge of the Quarantine Camp shall, at the time of release of an animal from the`
  line `station, grant a permit, in such form as may be prescribed by the State Government, to the person taking`
  line `charge of the animal, and every such person shall be bound to produce the permit whenever required to do`
  line `so by any Competent Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (1704)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Inspection and detention of animals at Check Posts and Quarantine Camps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1704&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every`
  line `person in charge of any Check Post or Quarantine Camp shall inspect any animal stopped at the Check`
  line `Post, or detained therein or at the Quarantine Camp.`
  line
  line `(2) The manner of inspection and the period of detention of the animal at the Check Post or at the`
  line `Quarantine Camp for the purpose of inspection or for the administration of compulsory vaccination, the`
  line `marking of animals and the form and manner in which permit for entry in respect of any animal may be`
  line `issued, shall be such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (1705)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Entry and exit of vaccinated animals into controlled and free areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1705&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line Notwithstanding
  line `anything contained in section 10, an animal belonging to the species of animals in respect of which an`
  line `area has been declared as a controlled or free area in relation to any scheduled disease, which has been`
  line `duly vaccinated against that disease, shall be allowed to enter into or be taken out of the controlled area or`
  line `free area, or to be taken out of any other place on the production of a certificate to the effect that vaccine`
  line `against that disease has been administered and a period of not less than twenty-one days has elapsed`
  line thereafter.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (1706)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Appointment of Competent Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1706&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, for the proper`
  line `implementation of the provisions of this Act, by notification, authorise any person to exercise any power`
  line `or discharge any duty as a Competent Officer, under this Act, who shall exercise such powers and such`
  line `duties within the local limits of his jurisdiction as may be specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (1707)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Cleaning and disinfection of carriers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1707&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every common carrier whether a vessel or vehicle`
  line `shall be cleaned and disinfected immediately before and after the transportation of any animal in that`
  line `vessel or vehicle, and so also any other place where the animal has been kept in transit.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any area has been declared as a controlled area or free area in respect of any scheduled`
  line `disease affecting any species of animal, the Director may, by an order duly published in the Official`
  line `Gazette and in a local newspaper in the vernacular language, direct the owner of every vehicle in which`
  line `any animal belonging to that species is carried, to have the vehicle properly cleaned and disinfected.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (1708)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Powers of entry and inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1708&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Any Veterinary Officer or other Competent Officer may enter`
  line `upon and inspect any land or building or place, vessel or vehicle, for the purpose of ensuring compliance`
  line `of the provisions of this Act or the rules or orders made thereunder, by the persons responsible for such`
  line compliance.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (1709)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Declaration of infected areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1709&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `If the Veterinary Officer, upon receipt of a report from a`
  line `Veterinarian or otherwise, is satisfied that, in any place or premises falling within his jurisdiction, an`
  line `animal has been infected with any scheduled disease, or that an animal, which he has reason to believe`
  line `has been so infected, is kept, may, by notification and publication in at least one local newspaper in the`
  line `vernacular language and by declaration in loud voice and by beating drums, declare such area as he may`
  line `deem fit (including the place or premises aforesaid) to be an infected area.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (1710)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Effect of declaration of infected areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1710&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an area has been declared as an infected`
  line `area under section 20, all provisions of this Act which are applicable in relation to a controlled area shall`
  line `mutatis mutandis apply thereto as if for the words "controlled area", the words "infected area" have been`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions contained in sub-section (1), the following`
  line `further provisions shall apply in relation to an infected area, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of every animal in that area which is infected or reasonably believed to be infected,`
  line `with any scheduled disease, the owner or other person in charge of the animal, shall forthwith get it`
  line `treated by a Veterinarian;`
  line
  line `(b) all articles, which are likely to have come into contact with any animal referred to in`
  line `clause (a), shall be treated or disposed off in such a manner as the Veterinarian may direct;`
  line
  line `(c) every Veterinarian shall, for the purpose of inspection, have the power to enter any place or`
  line `premises where any animal is kept or is likely to be kept;`
  line
  line `(d) the owner or any other person in charge of the animal referred to in clause (a) shall keep the`
  line `animal in isolation forthwith, and also take such other measures as may be necessary for the`
  line `prevention, treatment and control of the disease as the Veterinarian may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (1711)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Denotification of infected area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1711&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `If the Veterinary Officer, after such enquiry as he may deem`
  line `fit, is satisfied that there is no longer the threat or danger of any animal being infected with the scheduled`
  line `disease in any infected area, by notification and publication in a local newspaper in vernacular language,`
  line `declare that the area is no longer an infected area as aforesaid, whereupon all the restrictions referred to in`
  line `section 21 shall cease to apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (1712)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Segregation, examination and treatment of infected animals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1712&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Veterinarian`
  line `has, on receipt of a report or otherwise, reason to believe that any animal is infected with a scheduled`
  line `disease, he may, by order in writing, direct the owner or any other person in charge of such animal--`
  line
  line `(a) to keep it segregated from other apparently healthy animals; or`
  line
  line `(b) to subject it to such treatment as may be required under the circumstances.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any action has been taken in pursuance of sub-section (1), the Veterinarian shall forthwith`
  line `give a detailed report of the incidence of the disease to the Veterinary Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of a report from the Veterinarian, the Veterinary Officer shall, as soon as possible,`
  line `examine that animal as well as any other animal which could have come in contact with it, and for that`
  line `purpose, submit the animal to such test and medical examination as may be required under the`
  line circumstances.
  line
  line `(4) If, after such test and examination, the Veterinary Officer is of the opinion that an animal is not`
  line `infected with any of the scheduled diseases, he shall issue a certificate in writing that the animal is not`
  line `infected with any such disease.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (1713)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Drawing samples from animals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1713&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Veterinary Officer considers it necessary for`
  line `the purpose of ascertaining whether the animal which is suspected to have been infected with any`
  line `scheduled disease or susceptible to such infection is actually infected, or for the purpose of ascertaining`
  line `the nature of the scheduled disease with which an animal is infected, he may draw such samples, as may`
  line `be required, from the animal for the purpose of carrying out such investigations as he may deem`
  line `necessary under the circumstances.`
  line
  line `(2) The Veterinary Officer or any other Competent Officer shall draw samples from any animal for`
  line `the purposes of ascertaining whether the animal has been vaccinated against any disease, or whether the`
  line `vaccination of the animal has been effective in conferring it immunity and have the samples examined, in`
  line `such manner as he may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (1714)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Resort to euthanasia for infected animals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1714&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `If the Veterinary Officer deems it necessary that an`
  line `animal, which is infected with a scheduled disease, euthanasia has to be resorted to, for preventing the`
  line `spread of the disease to other animals in the area or to protect public health if the disease is of zoonotic`
  line `importance, he may, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, by`
  line `an order in writing, direct euthanasia of the animal and the carcass disposed of immediately to his`
  line satisfaction.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (1715)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Disposal of carcass.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1715&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Every person in possession of carcass (or any part thereof) of any animal,`
  line `which, at the time of its death, was infected with any scheduled disease or was suspected to have been`
  line `infected, shall dispose it of in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (1716)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Powers of Veterinary Officer and Veterinarian to hold post-mortem examinations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1716&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Where the Veterinary Officer or any Veterinarian has reason to believe that the death of an animal has`
  line `been caused by an infection of any scheduled disease, he may make or cause to be made a post-mortem`
  line `examination of the animal and for that purpose he may cause the carcass of any such animal to be`
  line `exhumed where required followed by proper disposal after necessary examination and post-mortem.`
  line
  line `(2) Every examination and post-mortem referred to in sub-section (1) shall be conducted in such`
  line `manner, and the report of post-mortem shall be in such form, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (1717)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Seizure and removal of certain animals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1717&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Where any animal which is infected or suspected to`
  line `have been infected is found without any person claiming to be its owner, or where a valid order or`
  line `direction given in relation to any such animal is not promptly complied with by the owner or other person`
  line `in control of the animal, it shall be open to the Veterinary Officer or any other Competent Officer, to seize`
  line `the animal and remove it to a place of isolation or segregation, as he may deem proper.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (1718)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Enforcement of orders and recovery of expenses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1718&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where by any rule, notification, notice,`
  line `requisition, order or direction made under this Act, any person is required to take any measure or to do`
  line anything--
  line
  line `(a) in respect of any animal, carcass of any animal or other thing in his custody or charge, the`
  line `same shall be promptly complied with by that person;`
  line
  line `(b) in case of any stray or ownerless animal, carcass of such animal or parts thereof, the same`
  line `shall be promptly complied with by the municipality or Panchayat, as the case may be, at its cost.`
  line
  line `(2) If the measures as referred to in sub-section (1) are not taken within such time as may be allowed`
  line `for the purpose, the authority issuing the notice, requisition, order or direction, may cause the measures to`
  line `be taken at the cost of the person or municipality or Panchayat, as the case may be, who or which was`
  line `required to take the measures.`
  line
  line `(3) The costs of any measures taken under sub-section (2), shall be recoverable from the person or the`
  line `municipality or Panchayat, as the case may be, concerned in the manner provided by the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) for the recovery of fines imposed by a Court, as if such costs were a`
  line `fine imposed by a Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (1719)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Village Officers, etc., to assist.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1719&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `All Municipal, Panchayat or Village Officers and all officers of`
  line `the rural and dairy development, revenue, agriculture, animal husbandry and veterinary departments of`
  line `the State Government, shall be bound--`
  line
  line `(a) to give immediate information to the Veterinary Officer and to the Veterinarian having`
  line `jurisdiction in the area regarding the prevalence of a scheduled disease amongst any animal or species`
  line `of animals, in the area;`
  line
  line `(b) to take all necessary measures to prevent the outbreak or spread of any scheduled disease; and`
  line
  line `(c) to assist the Veterinary Officer and the Veterinarian in the discharge of their duties or in the`
  line `exercise of their powers under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (1720)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Penalty for issuing vaccination certificate without authority or administering defective vaccine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1720&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `If any person issues a vaccination certificate,--`
  line
  line `(a) without authority or competence in that behalf, or`
  line
  line `(b) after administering the vaccine which is known to be defective in any manner,`
  line
  line `he shall be guilty of an offence punishable with a fine of five thousand rupees or in case of non-payment`
  line `of fine with imprisonment which may extend to one month, and in the case of any subsequent offence,`
  line `with fine of ten thousand rupees or with imprisonment which may extend to three months.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (1721)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1721&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Any person who contravenes the provisions of this Act or obstructs the Competent`
  line `Officer in performing his duties shall be guilty of an offence punishable with fine which may extend to`
  line `one thousand rupees, and in case of failure to pay the penalty with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to one month; and in the case of any subsequent offence (whether under the same provision or any`
  line `other provision of this Act except in case of sections 31 and 33) with a fine of two thousand rupees, or`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two months in case of non-payment of the penalty.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (1722)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Penalty for placing infected animal or carcass in river, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1722&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Whoever places or causes or`
  line `permits to be placed in any river, lake, canal or any other water body, the carcass or any part of the`
  line `carcass of any animal which at the time of its death was known to be infected, shall be guilty of an`
  line `offence and, on conviction, be punished, in the case of a first offence with fine of two thousand rupees or`
  line `with imprisonment of one month in case of non-payment of fine and in the case of subsequent conviction`
  line `with a fine of five thousand rupees or imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months or with`
  line both.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (1723)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1723&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render such person liable to any punishment`
  line `provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had`
  line `exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a co-operative society registered or`
  line `deemed to be registered under any law for the time being in force, a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (1724)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Prevention of escape of causative organism.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1724&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every institution, laboratory or clinic,`
  line `engaged in the manufacture, testing or research, related to vaccines, sera, diagnostics or chemotherapeutic`
  line `drugs and aimed at the prevention or treatment of any scheduled disease, adequate precautionary`
  line `measures shall be taken--`
  line
  line `(a) to ensure that the causative organism of any scheduled disease does not escape or otherwise`
  line `get released;`
  line
  line `(b) to guard against any such escape or release; and`
  line
  line `(c) to warn and to protect everyone concerned in the event of any escape.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, every animal--`
  line
  line `(a) used for the manufacture, testing or research as referred to sub-section (1), or`
  line
  line `(b) which is likely to carry or transmit any scheduled disease,`
  line
  line `shall be promptly administered euthanasia and disposed of by the person in charge of or having control of`
  line `the institution, laboratory or clinic, as the case may be, referred to in that sub-section.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person who is in charge of or having control of an institution, laboratory or clinic referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1) comply with the provisions of sub-section (1) and sub-section (2); and in the event of`
  line `non-compliance he shall be guilty of an offence punishable with fine which may extend to twenty`
  line `thousand rupees or imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with both, and in case the`
  line `establishment is in commercial manufacturing of vaccines or medicine, a temporary suspension of licence`
  line `up to a period of one year may also be imposed.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (1725)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1725&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by notification, delegate to any officer or`
  line `authority subordinate to it, all or any of the powers conferred on it by or under this Act, except the powers`
  line `to make rules under sub-section (2) of section 42.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (1726)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Officers and authorities to function subject to Government control.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1726&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `All officers and`
  line `authorities under this Act shall exercise their powers and discharge their duties conferred or imposed on`
  line `them by or under this Act, in accordance with such orders, not inconsistent with the provisions of this`
  line `Act, as the Central Government or the State Government may, from time to time, make.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (1727)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power to amend the Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1727&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, add to, or`
  line `omit from the Schedule any animal disease and the said disease shall, as from the date of the notification,`
  line `be deemed to have been added to, or omitted from, the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification issued under sub-section (1) shall, as soon as may be after it is issued, be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (1728)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1728&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, with the object of prevention, control`
  line `and eradication of any infectious or contagious disease of animals, issue such directions to the State`
  line `Government or other authorities under this Act, from time to time, including directions for furnishing`
  line `such returns and statistics on scheduled diseases, and vaccination, as it may deem fit and every such`
  line `direction shall be complied with.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (1729)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Certain persons to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1729&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Every Competent Officer, Director and Veterinary`
  line `Officer, while exercising any power or performing any duty under this Act, shall be deemed to be a public`
  line `servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (1730)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1730&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (1731)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1731&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, subject to`
  line `the condition of previous publication, by notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form of vaccination certificate and the particulars which such certificate shall contain,`
  line `under section 9;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of disposal of carcass, under section 26;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of conducting examination and post-mortem under sub-section (1) and the form of`
  line `report of post-mortem under sub-section (2) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which may be prescribed or in respect of which rules are required to be made`
  line `by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (1732)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1732&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification`
  line `and with the prior approval of the Central Government, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form of permit to be granted by the officer in charge of a Quarantine Camp, under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of inspection and the period of detention of an animal at a Check Post or at a`
  line `Quarantine Camp for the administration of compulsory vaccination and marking of animals and the`
  line `form and manner of issue of entry permit, under sub-section (2) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter in respect of which rule is to be or may be made by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (1733)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Laying of rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1733&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period`
  line `of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if,`
  line `before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid,`
  line `both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be`
  line `made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (1734)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569&sectionId=1734&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_62_00007_200927_1517807327569
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `On the commencement of this Act--`
  line
  line `(i) The Glanders and Farcy Act, 1899 (13 of 1899);`
  line
  line `(ii) The Dourine Act, 1910 (5 of 1910); and`
  line
  line `(iii) any other corresponding law of any State, so far as it is inconsistent with the provisions of`
  line `this Act,`
  line
  line `shall stand repealed:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall--`
  line
  line `(a) affect the previous operation of any such provision of law or anything duly done or suffered`
  line thereunder;
  line
  line `(b) affect any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under any such`
  line `provision of law;`
  line
  line `(c) affect any penalty, forfeiture or punishment incurred in respect of any offence committed`
  line `against any such provision of law; or`
  line
  line `(d) affect any investigation, legal proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege,`
  line `obligation, liability, penalty, forfeiture or punishment as aforesaid; and every such investigation, legal`
  line `proceeding or remedy may be continued, instituted or enforced, and any such penalty, forfeiture and`
  line `punishment may be imposed, as if the aforesaid provisions of law had continued:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, anything done or any action taken under any such provision of law, including`
  line `any notification, order, notice or receipt issued or declaration made, shall in so far as it is not inconsistent`
  line `with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been done, taken, issued or made under the`
  line `corresponding provisions of this Act, and shall continue in force accordingly, unless and until superseded`
  line `by anything done or any action taken under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
